2362 // testRDIV -
2363 // When we have a pair of subscripts of the form [c1 + a1*i] and [c2 + a2*j]
2364 // where i and j are induction variables, c1 and c2 are loop invariant,
2365 // and a1 and a2 are constant, we can solve it exactly with an easy adaptation
2366 // of the Exact SIV test, the Restricted Double Index Variable (RDIV) test.
2367 // It doesn't make sense to talk about distance or direction in this case,
2368 // so there's no point in making special versions of the Strong SIV test or
2369 // the Weak-crossing SIV test.
2370 //
2371 // Return true if dependence disproved.
